SHELL

Functionalities:
1. Execute all the commands (ls, clear, vi etc) 
2. Shell built­ins (cd, pwd, export) 
3. Print environment variables and text using echo 
4. I/O redirection (<, >)
5. Pipes “|” (multiple) 
6. Support for history and '!' operator 
7. Handle   Interrupt   Signal:   On   pressing   "Ctrl+C",   the   command   that   is   running   currently terminates. 
